<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>User Dashboard</title>
  <style>
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #74ABE2, #5563DE);
      color: #333;
      height: 100vh;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    nav {
      background: white;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 15px 30px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    nav h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      color: #5563DE;
    }

    nav button {
      background-color: #f44336;
      border: none;
      color: white;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-size: 15px;
      transition: background 0.3s;
    }

    nav button:hover {
      background-color: #d7382e;
    }

    .content {
      flex: 1;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      color: white;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .content h2 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .content p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      max-width: 400px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <nav>
    <h1>My Dashboard</h1>
    <form action="/logout" method="POST" style="margin: 0;">
      <button type="submit">Logout</button>
    </form>
  </nav>

  <div class="content">
    <h2>Welcome, <span id="username"><%= name %></span>!</h2>
    <p>You’ve successfully logged in. This is your dashboard — where you can access your personal data, settings, or any other features you plan to add.</p>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
